{"id": "general_lmsys_chat_1m_2300_289495", "question": "Problem : Write a C++ 17 program to implement the Knapsack algorithm to solve the 0/1 Knapsack problem. Give me full source code with main method included and dont explain anything in output. \nInput: int values[] = {60, 100, 120}; int weights[] = {10, 20, 30}; int W = 50;\nOutput : 220", "answer": "```c\n#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint knapsack(int values[], int weights[], int W) {\n    sort(weights.begin(), weights.end());\n    sort(values.begin(), values.end());\n    int n = values.size();\n    vector<bool> used(n);\n    int result = 0;\n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n        int value = values[i];\n        int weight = weights[i];\n        if (value <= W) {\n            result += value;\n            used[i] = true;\n        }\n        while (i < n && used[i]) {\n            int weight_i = weights[i];\n            int value_i = values[i];\n            if (weight_i < weight) {\n                result += value_i;\n                used[i] = false;\n            } else if (weight_i == weight) {\n                result += Math.min(value_i, result);\n                used[i] = false;\n            }\n            i++;\n        }\n    }\n    return result;\n}\n\nint main() {\n    int values[] = {60, 100, 120};\n    int weights[] = {10, 20, 30};\n    int W = 50;\n    int result = knapsack(values, weights, W);\n    cout << \"Result: \" << result << endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n```"}
